Applications of Coherent Infrared Synchrotron Radiation http www als lbl gov als usermtg index html Applications of Coherent Infrared Synchrotron Radiation 2002 ALS Users Meeting Workshop October 11 2002 Scope This workshop will focus on scientific applications of and plans for a coherent far IR 1 100 cm 1 synchrotron source which will have intensities 5 to 6 orders of magnitude higher than conventional far IR sources We hope to use this workshop to further explore different types of science which could be enabled by such a novel source in this traditionally difficult spectral region Summary http infrared als lbl gov pubs SRN 16 1 8 IRWorkshop2002 pdf Workshop on applications of coherent infrared synchrotron radiation Michael C Martin Synchrotron Radiation News 16 8 2003 Program IRworkshop02sched html Workshop Program Location LBNL Building 70 Room 191 http www lbl gov Workplace Transportation html Directions to LBNL Speakers Tatiana Globus University of Virginia George Neil Jefferson Lab John Byrd LBNL Erik Helgren UCLA Ulrich Schade BESSY Germany E Jason Singley LBNL Michael Martin LBNL Registration Please use the main http www als lbl gov als usermtg registration html ALS Users Meeting Registration Form and select that you will be attending the infrared workshop Workshop Organizing Committee Michael Martin and Wayne McKinney Advanced Light Source Dimitri Basov UC San Diego Joe Orenstein UC Berkeley For more information about this workshop contact Michael Martin or Wayne McKinney Advanced Light Source mailto MCMartin lbl gov MCMartin lbl gov mailto WRMcKinney lbl gov WRMcKinney lbl gov 510 495 2231 510 486 4395 http www lbl gov Disclaimers html Privacy and Security Notice mailto mcmartin lbl gov mcmartin lbl gov ALS index html IR Beamlines http www als lbl gov als usermtg Users Meeting Home http www als lbl gov ALS Home Page
